"Starting from Android M (6.0), the system requires apps to be granted location access in order to scan for BLE devices.
If you've previously granted the app location permission before, this is because the app now targets Android Q (10) and is required to prompt you for a different level of location permission.
Your location is never actually used aside from enabling the app to perform BLE scans."
